# Block system

WordPress HTML → `BlockRenderer` → React block → React Query hook → `lib/block.js` GraphQL.

## Adding a new block (all steps required)

1. CMS outputs `<div id="block-{name}" data-block-identifier-id="...">`
2. Create `src/app/components/block/{Name}Block.js` with `'use client'`
3. Register in `BLOCK_MAP` in `BlockRenderer.js` (`startsWith: true` if ID has a dynamic suffix)
4. Add `GetPageWith{Name}(slug, preferTranslation = false)` in `lib/block.js`
5. Add `use{Name}()` in `hooks/useBlockQueries.js` (include `slug` + `isTH` in `queryKey`)
6. Add styles in `css/scss/main.scss`

## Component conventions

- Merge CMS `class` → `className` (attribs use HTML `class`, not React `className`)
- Match multi-instance blocks via `data-block-identifier-id` / `blockIdentifierId`; fallback index map if needed (see `RetailInformationBlock.js`)
- Loading: skeleton UI; error/empty: return `null`
- Prefer React Query hooks over `useEffect` + direct lib calls for new work
- Keep GreenShift classes (`wp-block-greenshift-blocks-swiper`, `gs-swiper`, etc.)

```js
// ✅ Register with startsWith when IDs are like block-retail-information-abc
{ id: 'block-retail-information', component: RetailInformationBlock, startsWith: true }
```
